"""stage2.bzl: developer tools built from source with Bazel, inside the
hermetic Linux sandbox (--experimental_use_hermetic_linux_sandbox) without
mounting anything from the host. The name marks the trust boundary: from
stage 2 of the bootstrap onward, no action has any prebuilt binary among
its inputs.

First tool: the riscv-none-elf GCC toolchain.

The first tools are GNU cross toolchains built from these components:
  - GCC 15.2.0
  - binutils 2.45
  - newlib 4.5.0
  - target riscv-none-elf, default architecture rv32imac/ilp32

Because the sandbox root is empty (no /bin, /lib, /usr, not even /bin/sh),
every build prerequisite is a pinned download that runs standalone:
  - host C/C++ compiler: musl.cc static native toolchain (GCC 11.2.1);
    static binaries need no ELF interpreter, so they exec in an empty root,
    and -static makes every binary they produce equally self-sufficient;
  - bootstrap shell + userland: Alpine's busybox-static, used only until
    the from-source GNU userland (bash, coreutils, ...) is built;
  - GNU make: bootstrapped from source via its shipped build.sh, which is
    designed to build make without an existing make.
"""

module(
    name = "stage2.bzl",
    version = "1.0.0",
    bazel_compatibility = [">=9.0.0"],
)

bazel_dep(name = "platforms", version = "1.1.0")

http_archive = use_repo_rule("@bazel_tools//tools/build_defs/repo:http.bzl", "http_archive")

http_file = use_repo_rule("@bazel_tools//tools/build_defs/repo:http.bzl", "http_file")

_SRC_TREE_BUILD = """filegroup(
    name = "srcs",
    srcs = glob(["**"]),
    visibility = ["//visibility:public"],
)
exports_files(["configure"])
"""

